JSSE for 1.3.1 has a seed-generation bug on startup that causes long  
delays.

On Wednesday, July 9, 2003, at 11:14 AM, James Asher wrote:

> When I run my test using java 1.3 I get a time of
> about 48 seconds.  When I run it using java 1.4 I get
> a time of about 17 seconds.  The only difference
> between each test is that one is run using java 1.3
> and the other java 1.4.  Is this supposed to happen?
> Could it be just the java version? or could it be bad
> coding on my part? Or perhaps the fact that I'm using
> JSSE and that it's already apart of java 1.4 and not
> 1.3 and there is some sort of time saving part in
> there that I'm not aware of.
>
> Thank you for your comments.
>
>  - James
